baseline_templates.name: Foundational Growth (3-Day Full Body)
baseline_templates.reasoning: Full-body training 3x/week maximizes beginner 'newbie gains' by hitting each muscle group frequently. Compound movements build a strong foundation while keeping volume manageable for recovery.

baseline_templates.name: Sculpt & Strength (3-Day Full Body)
baseline_templates.reasoning: Leverages women's generally higher fatigue resistance with slightly higher rep ranges. Emphasis on posterior chain (glutes/hamstrings) and balanced upper body development.

baseline_templates.name: Hypertrophy PPL (Push/Pull/Legs)
baseline_templates.reasoning: The classic Push/Pull/Legs split allows high volume per muscle group while training each muscle twice per week — the sweet spot for hypertrophy. Ideal for intermediate lifters who've outgrown full-body routines.

baseline_templates.name: Upper/Lower Hypertrophy Split
baseline_templates.reasoning: A 4-day Upper/Lower split balances volume and recovery perfectly for intermediates who can't commit to 6 days. Each muscle is trained twice per week with ample recovery between sessions.

baseline_templates.name: Powerlifting Foundation (4-Day)
baseline_templates.reasoning: Built around the big 3 (squat, bench, deadlift) with dedicated days for each. Lower rep ranges with longer rest periods build maximal strength. Accessories target weak points in the main lifts.

baseline_templates.name: Longevity Strength (Upper/Lower)
baseline_templates.reasoning: Accounts for slower systemic recovery in 40+ athletes. Uses an Upper/Lower split to prevent joint overuse while maintaining high intensity on primary lifts.

baseline_templates.name: Vitality & Balance (2-Day Full Body)
baseline_templates.reasoning: Prioritizes functional mobility, bone density, and fall prevention. Lower volume and higher rest periods to accommodate slower recovery. Includes balance-specific movements.

baseline_templates.name: Metabolic Power (PPL)
baseline_templates.reasoning: High-frequency training to maximize caloric expenditure while preserving lean muscle during a calorie deficit. Shorter rest periods increase metabolic demand. Compound movements burn more calories.

baseline_templates.name: No Equipment Needed (3-Day Bodyweight)
baseline_templates.reasoning: A complete bodyweight program requiring zero equipment. Perfect for home workouts or travel. Progressive overload through reps, tempo, and exercise variations.

baseline_templates.name: HIIT Fat Burner (3-Day)
baseline_templates.reasoning: High-intensity interval training burns maximum calories in minimum time. The EPOC (afterburn) effect means you keep burning calories hours after the workout. Perfect for busy schedules and fat loss goals.

baseline_templates.name: Dumbbell-Only Gains (4-Day)
baseline_templates.reasoning: Complete muscle-building program using only dumbbells. Perfect for home gyms or limited equipment. Upper/Lower split ensures each muscle is hit twice per week for optimal growth.

baseline_templates.name: Advanced Hypertrophy PPL
baseline_templates.reasoning: High-volume program for advanced lifters who need more stimulus to continue growing. Incorporates intensity techniques, varied rep ranges, and strategic exercise selection to push past plateaus.

baseline_templates.name: Lean & Strong (4-Day)
baseline_templates.reasoning: Combines resistance training with metabolic conditioning to build lean muscle while burning fat. Focus on compound movements for maximum calorie burn and a toned, athletic physique.

baseline_templates.name: Balanced Fitness (3-Day Full Body)
baseline_templates.reasoning: A well-rounded program balancing strength, endurance, and mobility. Perfect for anyone who wants to look good, feel good, and move well without committing to a bodybuilding split.

baseline_templates.name: Resistance Band Revolution (Full Body)
baseline_templates.reasoning: A comprehensive home-based program using only resistance bands. This routine maximizes muscle tension through constant resistance, perfect for those without gym access or who prefer home workouts.

baseline_templates.name: Machine Mastery: Advanced Bodybuilder Split
baseline_templates.reasoning: Focuses on maximizing hypertrophy through stable, machine-based movements. This allows for extreme intensity and isolation while minimizing joint stress. Perfect for advanced lifters looking to bring up weak points with high precision.

baseline_templates.name: The Functional Kettlebell (3-Day)
baseline_templates.reasoning: Utilizes the unique loading of kettlebells to build stability, power, and functional strength. High carryover to real-world movements and athletics.
